Brigadier General Anthony J. Tata, a retired United States Army officer, has been nominated to be the Under Secretary of Defense for Policy. He currently serves as the Senior Advisor to the Secretary of Defense. General Tata has a diverse background, including being the President and CEO of Tata Leadership Group, LLC, as well as the COO of Washington, D.C. Public Schools. He has also held various positions within the United States Army, including Deputy Director of the Joint Improvised Explosive Device Defeat Organization and Commander of the 2nd Brigade, 101st Airborne Division. General Tata is a decorated veteran and a graduate of the United States Military Academy.

David Reimer, a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, has been nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Sierra Leone. He currently serves as the United States Ambassador to the Republic of Mauritius and the Republic of Seychelles. Ambassador Reimer has extensive experience in diplomatic roles, including serving as the Director in the Office of West African Affairs at the Department of State and as the Deputy Chief of Mission of the United States Embassy in Nouakchott, Mauritania.

David E. Richardson has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Homeland Security for Countering Weapons of Mass Destruction. Andrew Rakowsky has been nominated to be a Member of the Federal Salary Council.